# Running Tests in Playwright

1️⃣ What Does "Running Tests" Mean?
Running tests means executing automated test scripts to verify that the application behaves as expected.
In Playwright  , tests can be executed using:
    1. Playwright CLI
    2. Pytest Framework
    3. Command line
    4. IDE/ Test Runner
👉 Simple definition:
    Running tests = Executing Playwright automation scripts to validate application behavior

2️⃣ Ways to Run Playwright Tests
Playwright tests can be executed in several ways:
    1. Using pytest command
    2. Running specific test files
    3. Running specific test cases
    4. Running tests in headless/headed mode
    5. Running tests in parallel

3️⃣ Running Tests Using Pytest
Most playwright python frameworks use pytest.
Basic command:
    pytest
This command , 
    1. finds all test files
    2. execute all test cases
Example test file:
    test_login.py
Example test case:
    def test_login(page):
        page.goto("https://example.com")
    
4️⃣ Test File Naming Convention
Pytest follows naming rules to identify test files.
Valid names:
    1. test_login.py
    2. test_checkout.py
    3. test_search.py

Test function naming:
    1. def test_login():
    2. det test_checkout():

Rules:
    1. File name starts with test_
    3. Function name starts with test_

5️⃣ Running a Specific Test File
To run a single test file:
    syntax:
        pytest <file_name>
    Example:
        pytest test_login.py
    Only that file will run.

6️⃣ Running a Specific Test Case
To run a specific test case:
    pytest test_login.py::test_valid_login
Example:
    pytest test_checkout.py::test_payment
This runs only one test case

7️⃣ Running Tests in Headless Mode
Headless mode runs tests without opening the browser UI.
Command:
    pytest
By default Playwright uses headless in CI environments.
Advantages:
    1. Faster execution
    2. USed in CI/CD pipelines

8️⃣ Running Tests in Headed Mode
Headed mode opens the browser UI while executing tests.
Example:
    pytest --headed

Benefits:
    1. Useful for debugging
    2. Helps visualization automation.

9️⃣ Running Tests in Parallel
Playwright supports parallel test execution.
Example command:
    pytest -n 4

Meaning:
    Run test in 4 parallel workers

Benefits:
    1. Faster execution
    2. Reduced  test time

NOTE:
    Required pytest-xdist plugin.
Install
    pip install pytest-xdist

🔟 Running Tests with Verbose Output
Verbose mode shows detailed test results.
Command :
    pytest -v

Output example:
    test_login.py::test_valid_login PASSED
    test_logib.py::test_invalid_login FAILED

1️⃣1️⃣ Running Tests with HTML Report
Generate HTML test report.
Example:
    pytest --html=report.html

Install plugin:
    pip install pytest-html

Benefits:
    1. Visual test results
    2. Useful for reporting

1️⃣2️⃣ Running Tests by Markers
Pytest allows grouping tests using markers.
Example:
    import pytest
    @pytest.mark.smoke
    def test_login():
        pass
    
    Run smoke tests:
        pytest -m smoke

    Example markers:
        Marker & Purpose
        -----------------
        1. smoke -> Basic tests
        2. regression -> full testing
        3. sanity -> quick validation
    
1️⃣3️⃣ Running Tests with Debug Mode
for debugging tests:
    pytest --pdb

Open python debugger when test fails.

1️⃣4️⃣ Running Tests with Playwright Debug Mode
Playwright provides debugging tools.
Example:
    PWDDEBUG=1 pytest
Features:
    1. step-by-step execution
    2. Inspector tool
    3. DOM inspection

1️⃣5️⃣ Running Tests with Trace Viewer
Trace viewer records test execution.
Example:
    pytest --trace on

View trace:
    playwright show-trace trace.zip

Trace shows:
    1. screenshots
    2. network calls
    3. actions
    4. DOM snapshots
Useful for debugging failues

1️⃣6️⃣ Running Tests in CI/CD
Playwright tests can run in CI tools like:
    1. Jenkins
    2. GitHub Actions
    3. GitLab CI
    4. Azure DevOps

Example CI command:
    pytest
Typically executed in headless mode.

1️⃣7️⃣ Real Example
Example test file:
    def test_login(page):

    page.goto("https://example.com")

    page.get_by_label("Username").fill("admin")
    page.get_by_label("Password").fill("admin123")

    page.get_by_role("button", name="Login").click()


run command:
    pytest test_login.py

1️⃣8️⃣ Common Test Execution Flow
Typical flow when running tests:
    1. Pytest discovered test files
    2. Browser is launched
    3. Browser context is created
    4. Test steps execute
    5. Assertion validate results
    6. Tests results are generated

1️⃣9️⃣ Common Errors While Running Tests
1. ModuleNotFoundError
Occurs when depenencies are missing.
Solution:
    pip install playwright

2. TimeoutError
Occurs when elements take too long.
Solution:
    Increase timeout or fix locator

2. Browser Not Installed
Solution:
    playwright install


